Patch Set 7: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(3 inline comments)

Firstly: @Arnaud, Code looks awesome!

This implementation seems amazingly clean and straightforward at the executor level. However, as we had the concerns before, some questions about the runtime below  - 

1. does it make sense to marry task-flow and glance for the complete execution logic?

2. Can we have a think executor logic placed on top of the TaskFlow executor which can be a good substitute for any other deployments?

3. How do we determine what backends could be used by the taskflow parallel engine? Wondering if that think layer mentioned above could prove useful to patch in a executor of "X" kind if/when Glance needs it?

4. Can we run multiple tasks using the serial eventlet executor? or does it limit the number of concurrent tasks to  1?

Will think about how the flow might help us themselves to address our plugin usecase.

Patch Set 7:

So some of these I can answer (and some I can't). Will give my best shot.

2. I hope that we can avoid to much executor logic ontop of the taskflow executor since that means that its executor isn't capable enough (which should be fixed). Hopefully any of these use-cases can be addressed as they occur (if any when they do).
3. Unsure about this one, can u explain in more depth, I'd hope that taskflow can satisfy the glance executor needs and for cases where it can't we work together to fix that in taskflow (since glance won't be the only place that a share library is used).
4. Serial executor limits to concurrency of 1, a parallel executor can be provided and used which will be restricted by the thread/greenthread pool size and the interdependencies between tasks and flows (a flow with less interdependencies between tasks can run at a higher concurrency rate than one with dependencies).
